      "review_summary": "The PR changes diagnostic session pruning to delete any entry older than the TTL and adds regression coverage for stale non-idle entries.\n\nPR surface: Source +2, Tests +29. Total +31 across 2 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. from source inspection. Failed recovery can leave a non-idle entry that current pruning never removes; the patch regression is also reproducible by aging a processing entry past the TTL and invoking a progress path that performs prune-before-lookup.",
