        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(logging): prune stale non-idle diagnostic session entries after TTL (fixes #91697)",
        "body": "### Summary\n\n- **Problem**: `pruneDiagnosticSessionStates()` only deletes entries where `state === \"idle\"` AND `queueDepth <= 0` AND `age > TTL`. Entries that never transition back to `\"idle\"` (e.g. after a failed stuck-session recovery) accumulate in the `diagnosticSessionStates` Map indefinitely, holding activity snapshots, tool call history, and queue metadata in V8 heap.\n- **Root Cause**: The prune loop in `pruneDiagnosticSessionStates()` has no fallback for stale non-idle entries. When `requestStuckSessionRecovery()` fails (e.g. stale generation check, already-closed session), the recovery outcome `{ status: \"failed\" }` skips the state-to-idle mutation, leaving the entry permanently in a non-idle state.\n- **Fix**: Add an `else if (ageMs > SESSION_STATE_TTL_MS)` fallback after the existing idle-gated deletion, so any entry exceeding the TTL is cleaned up regardless of state.\n- **What changed**:\n  - `src/logging/diagnostic-session-state.ts` — add fallback deletion for non-idle stale entries (2 lines)\n  - `src/logging/diagnostic.test.ts` — add regression test for non-idle TTL eviction; fix merge test timestamps to use realistic values instead of hardcoded `1`/`2`\n- **What did NOT change (scope boundary)**:\n  - No change to `SESSION_STATE_TTL_MS` (30 min) or `SESSION_STATE_PRUNE_INTERVAL_MS` (1 min)\n  - No change to the FIFO cap eviction path (still oldest-first by `lastActivity`)\n  - No change to stuck-session recovery logic or state mutation\n  - No change to `getDiagnosticSessionState` merge/alias behavior\n\n### Reproduction\n\n1. Gateway with `diagnostics.stuckSessionAbortMs` configured (e.g. 300000)\n2. A cron session stalls (DeepSeek mid-stream hang) → `stuckSessionAbortMs` fires\n3. Recovery fails (e.g. stale generation check, already-closed session)\n4. Outcome `{ status: \"failed\" }` skips mutation → state remains `\"processing\"`\n5. Entry lives in Map permanently because the prune loop only cleans `idle` entries\n\n### Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed (91697)**: `pruneDiagnosticSessionStates()` now cleans up stale diagnostic session entries that failed to transition back to idle after a failed stuck-session recovery, preventing unbounded heap accumulation.\n\n**Real environment tested**: Linux, Node 22 — fake-timer test harness against `pruneDiagnosticSessionStates`\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch**: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/logging/diagnostic.test.ts`\n\n**Evidence after fix**:\n```text\n[test] starting test/vitest/vitest.logging.config.ts\n\n RUN  v4.1.7 /home/0668001395/openclawProject1\n\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  69 passed (69)\n   Start at  01:17:12\n   Duration  8.03s (transform 6.25s, setup 871ms, import 6.50s, tests 402ms, environment 0ms)\n\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard in 16.60s\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix**: A non-idle (\"processing\") entry with `lastActivity` set 31 minutes in the past is pruned on the next `pruneDiagnosticSessionStates(now, true)` call, while a fresh idle entry survives. The new test case \"evicts stale non-idle session states after TTL\" confirms the stale non-idle entry is deleted and the fresh entry is preserved. All 68 existing tests in the diagnostic suite continue to behave correctly.\n\n**What was not tested**: Live Gateway round-trip with real stuck-session recovery failure and subsequent prune cycle was not driven; the fix was validated via the colocated diagnostic test suite with fake timers.\n\n**Repro confirmation**: The new test case \"evicts stale non-idle session states after TTL\" fails on origin/main before the patch (stale non-idle entry survives the prune — only idle entries are cleaned) and passes after the patch (stale non-idle entry is deleted).\n\n### Risk / Mitigation\n\n- **Risk**: The fallback deletion could theoretically clean up an active non-idle entry if its `lastActivity` is not being updated.\n  **Mitigation**: `SESSION_STATE_TTL_MS` is 30 minutes, and the prune interval is 1 minute. Any genuinely active session updates `lastActivity` on every activity event (state changes, queue updates, tool calls), well within the 30-minute window. The fallback only catches entries that have been dormant for >30 minutes.\n- **Risk**: The merge test timestamp change (from hardcoded `1`/`2` to `Date.now()`-relative values) could mask a timing issue.\n  **Mitigation**: The merge test tests alias resolution, not pruning. The timestamp change only ensures entries aren't falsely pruned by the new fallback during the merge test; the actual merge logic is unchanged.\n\n### Change Type (select all)\n\n- [x] Bug fix\n\n### Scope (select all touched areas)\n\n- [x] logging/diagnostics\n- [x] session-state\n\n### Regression Test Plan\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/logging/diagnostic.test.ts`\n\n### Review Findings Addressed\n\nN/A (initial submission)\n\n### Linked Issue/PR\n\nFixes #91697\n",
